to the editor how much homework should a teacher assign front page oct 10 the answer is easy the amount that can be reviewed in class the next day within 10 minutes for each subject homework that is not reviewed in class soon after it is assigned is of little value homework should represent a challenge or application of classwork both of which need reinforcement by the teacher if the teacher can not find the time students should not be required to give the time helen sultanik brooklyn oct 11 2000 the writer is the science coordinator for the board of jewish education

